
// This Hyperlambda code executes a workflow action named "html-encode-body" by invoking the [magic.workflows.actions.execute] slot. It specifies the file path of the workflow action and passes in an argument named [html] which is retrieved from the [.arguments] node's [body] child. The purpose is to perform HTML encoding on the provided body content.
execute:magic.workflows.actions.execute
   name:html-encode-body
   filename:/misc/workflows/actions/misc/html-encode.hl
   arguments
      html:x:@.arguments/*/body
